TriggerConfigurationService.createTriggerList(PlanKey planKey, @NotNull List<TriggerDefinition> triggerDefinitions);

appears to be a noop in TriggerConfigurationServiceImpl. It should be either implemented or deleted from the interface.

I've been looking into the method for our plugin where we create multiple triggers at the same time and I was hoping to avoid the multiple plan saves associated with createTrigger() method.

When the test xml to be parsed by bamboo contains only the {{testsuite}} tag without a nested {{testcase}}, the build fails with the message in the build logs stating that:
{code}
Failing task since test cases were expected but none were found.
{code}

The server logs on the hand shows that the test case was parsed with no test case:
{code}
2014-12-19 18:36:16,842 INFO [10-BAM::Default Agent::Agent:pool-25-thread-1] [TaskExecutorImpl] TESTA-GIT-JOB1-6: Starting task 'JUnit Parser' of type 'com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.testresult
parser:task.testresultparser.junit'
2014-12-19 18:36:16,883 INFO [pool-28-thread-1] [TestCollationServiceImpl] File /home/sultan/atlassianproducts/bamboo/atlassian-bamboo-5.7.2/HOME/xml-data/build-dir/TESTA-GIT-JOB1/test.xml parsing result: 0 successful, 0 failed, 0 skipped
{code}

It will be nice if we can implement and allow users to have a minimalistic test result especially that the Junit test result xml schema supports that.

When a downstream job prepares an artifacts shared by an upstream job, you get a message in the build log  along the lines of

{noformat}
Preparing artifact for use: XXX
Artifact XXX prepared in 0:00:00.856
{noformat}

For diagnostics, it'd be nice if this was a bit more verbose, such as logging the paths to which the artifact was prepared.

Under "{{Maven 3.x}}" task configuration, in order to have an external property loaded correctly, it is required to use the following syntax:
{noformat}
MAVEN_OPTS="-Xmx1024m" "-Dmy.property=${bamboo.myProperty}"
{noformat}
_Please, notice the space between the two properties._
!bamboo571.maven3x.png|thumbnail!

At moment, the current description is represented as per following:
{noformat}
Extra environment variables. e.g. MAVEN_OPTS="-Xmx256m -Xms128m". You can add multiple parameters separated by a space.
{noformat}
